[1] Taiwan ex China (Guangdong)
Date: Mon 6 Mar 2017
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/taiwan-reports-imported-measles-unvaccinated-child-26774/


Taiwan reports imported measles in unvaccinated child
-----------------------------------------------------
On [Fri 3 Mar 2017], the Taiwan Centers for Disease Control (Taiwan CDC) announced this year's [2017] 1st imported measles case in a 1 year old girl who resides in northern Taiwan and had not received the MMR (measles, mumps, and rubella) vaccine. According to health officials, she traveled to Guangdong, China with her family last October [2016].

On 22 Feb 2017, she developed fever and cough. On 26 Feb 2017, she developed rash. On 28 Feb 2017, she took Flight HX252 to return to Taiwan. Before she boarded the plane, she took a fever reducer. After she arrived at Taiwan Taoyuan International Airport at around 11 am, she was driven to a hospital for medical attention by her relative. She was reported to the health authority as a suspected case by the hospital and hospitalized in the isolation ward. On 3 Mar 2017, infection with measles was confirmed in the case after the hospital submitted her specimens for laboratory testing.

During the infectious period [22-28 Feb 2017, the case was in China for most of the time. To prevent further transmission of the disease, the local health authority has implemented a number of prevention measures and identified 144 contacts, including her family members who reside in the same household, passengers (including cabin crew) on the same flight, healthcare personnel, and patients that she came into contact with when she sought medical attention, to monitor and follow up until 18 Mar 2017.

Among the contacts, the case's brother sought medical attention in China after becoming infected with measles in mid-February [2017] and has since recovered. Currently, none of the other contacts has developed suspected symptoms. Individuals who met the criteria are being arranged for administration of immunoglobulin and MMR vaccine.

Last year [2016], a cumulative total of 14 measles cases, including 6 indigenous cases and 8 imported cases, were confirmed.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In addition to the 144 individuals alerted by the health authorities, everyone in the Hong Kong and Taiwan airports in the vicinity of the flight gates was exposed to measles virus.

Maps of the area can be seen at http://www.sacu.org/maps/provmap.png and http://www.healthmap.org/promed/?p=193.
